SIMPLE: odometer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: odometer
<hw>o*dom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(⟦osl⟧*d⟦ocr⟧m"⟦esl⟧*t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>"odo`metron</grk>, <grk>"odo`metros</grk>,
an instrument for measuring distance; <grk>"odo`s</grk> way +
<grk>me`tron</grk> measure: cf. F. <ets>odom⟦eacute⟧tre</ets>,
<ets>hodom⟦eacute⟧tre</ets>. See also <er>hodometer</er>.]</ety> <def>An
instrument attached to a vehicle or connected, as by a flexible cable,
to the wheel of a vehicle, which measures the distance
traversed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A <altname>hodometer</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>odometrical</ent>⟦br⟧
